U.S. regulators <a href="https://link.cfr.org/click/30817410.31898/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMy8wMy8xMi9idXNpbmVzcy9qYW5ldC15ZWxsZW4tc2lsaWNvbi12YWxsZXktYmFuay5odG1sP3V0bV9zb3VyY2U9ZGFpbHlicmllZg/5e137cf6ecf12a133a10a3b7B8671ec32" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">shut down (<em>NYT</em>)</a> New York–based Signature Bank yesterday, their second bank closure since Friday. To contain the fallout of the closures, authorities announced that they will fully guarantee deposits at both banks at no cost to U.S. taxpayers. Under normal circumstances, the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC) would only guarantee insured deposits of up to $250,000. Silicon Valley Bank, which closed first, <a href="https://link.cfr.org/click/30817410.31898/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAyMy8wMy8xMC9zaWxpY29uLXZhbGxleS1iYW5rLWlzLXNodXQtZG93bi1ieS1yZWd1bGF0b3JzLWZkaWMtdG8tcHJvdGVjdC1pbnN1cmVkLWRlcG9zaXRzLmh0bWw_dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1kYWlseWJyaWVm/5e137cf6ecf12a133a10a3b7Ba58a6835" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">was the country’s largest bank to fail (CNBC)</a> since the global financial crisis of 2008. 
</p><p><br/>President Joe Biden is due to give a speech about the bank failures this morning. In an effort to protect deposits, the Federal Reserve is <a href="https://link.cfr.org/click/30817410.31898/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTIvdXMtbW92ZXMtdG8taGVscC1kZXBvc2l0b3JzLW9mZmVyLWJhbmstYmFja3N0b3AtaW4td2FrZS1vZi1zdmI_c3JuZD1wcmVtaXVtJnNyZWY9dnhTelZEUDAmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1kYWlseWJyaWVm/5e137cf6ecf12a133a10a3b7B8e71f6fc" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">offering eligible banks (Bloomberg)</a> new one-year loans at favorable rates and easier access to its main direct lending facility.</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr>
