“The outline of the US government’s response to the failure of Silicon Valley Bank is now clear, and <a href="https://link.cfr.org/click/30817410.31898/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9CcmFkX1NldHNlci9zdGF0dXMvMTYzNTA1NjM2MjY4OTU0ODI5MT9zPTIwJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9ZGFpbHlicmllZg/5e137cf6ecf12a133a10a3b7Be52df9c3" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">the US didn’t mess around</a>. Clearly there was real concern about deposit flight and funding driven contagion,” CFR’s Brad Setser tweets.</p><p><br/>
